				\begin{document}$${\text{Percentage inhibition}} = 100 - \left( {\frac{{{\text{As}}}}{{{\text{Ab}}}} \times 100} \right)\% ,$$\end{document}Percentage inhibition=100-AsAb×100%,where As is absorbance of the sample and Ab is absorbance of the blank23.
